President Biden and First Lady Jill Biden will visit Surfside, Florida, to receive a command briefing on the search-and-rescue efforts and thank the first responders and search-and-rescue teams. They will also meet with the families affected by the building collapse and offer them comfort. The President will deliver remarks on the tragedy and the federal government's response efforts. FEMA has deployed over 60 staff members and 400 personnel from urban search-and-rescue teams to assist with the operations. FEMA has also awarded more than $20 million in federal funding to the Florida Division of Emergency Management. The National Institute of Standards and Technology will launch a full investigation into the collapse. The President believes the wealthiest Americans should pay their fair share and has announced initiatives to crack down on tax evasion. The President's focus today is on offering comfort, unity, and support to the community.